        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:24PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 823 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Algonac, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Marine City around 830 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Pearl Beach and Fair
Haven.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
